Project Reflection:

Platforms I Selected:


For my digital portfolio, I have set up and updated my profiles on the following three platforms:

GitHub: For hosting my code and technical projects.

LinkedIn: For professional networking and career building.

Kaggle: For practicing data science and machine learning skills.


Purpose of Each Platform:


I chose these because they help show different sides of my skills to future employers:

GitHub is like my digital notebook. It proves that I can actually write code and use version control (Git) to manage my work.

LinkedIn is my professional face. It’s where I can list my education, connect with experts in my field, and look for internship opportunities.

Kaggle is my practice ground. It allows me to work on real-world data problems and compete with other learners to improve my analytical thinking.


My FourYears Plan:


Over the next four years, I plan to stay active on these platforms to build a strong "digital footprint":

In first two years ,I will focus on uploading all my college lab work and small personal projects to GitHub to build a consistent "green" contribution graph.

In third year ,I will start sharing my certificates and project milestones on LinkedIn to get noticed by recruiters before internship season starts.

In Final year, I will use Kaggle to refine my portfolio with advanced projects, ensuring I have a high-quality showcase of my skills by the time I graduate.

